  "doc_id": "7331",
  "text": "One of the most important ability of OVs to attack cancer but not healthy cells is the selective replication ability. The selective replication of OVs could be achieved by taking advantage in several key-signaling pathways in cancer cells, including p53, interferon response pathway, epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) and Ras pathway, interferon-induced and doublestranded RNA-dependent protein kinase (PKR) pathways. Interestingly, these signaling pathways in cancer and normal cells are differently regulated by OVs [CITATION_1] [4] [CITATION_2] .",
